,"text":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTell us a little bit about yourself. How did you find your way to Condé Nast?\u003c/strong\u003eI’ve been employed here for 8 years now. My background is from the local music scene in Chicago where I was the program director at The Hideout, a beloved small venue. The Hideout produces an annual block party that gave me my large-scale concert-producing experience. I was initially hired here as a Marketing Associate, but over the last few years, have been able to steer my path into my passion, live events.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow do you describe your job to friends and family?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI describe it as a dream job on occasion! This job has allowed me to meet so many of my musical heroes, travel the world, and get such a deeper understanding of media and journalism. My family can hardly believe I am an Executive Director at such a big organization given my humble origins as a would-be actor and small club runner, but they are immensely proud of me.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat makes Mexico City such an exciting and special place to throw a music festival? What makes it challenging?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMexico City is such a vibrant and amazing city, I absolutely love visiting and get to frequently from my home of El Paso, TX. Our amazing partners in CDMX, Indie Rocks, who do the production of the festival on the ground are who make it such a wonderful festival that includes many local performers so that the relationship between Pitchfork and CDMX highlights some of their best artists and brings them to our audience’s attention. Challenges are that it's a first-year event, so just making sure we are out in the public and getting awareness on it is a huge goal.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWho do you think is the most underrated artist on the festival’s line-up?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI really love Debby Friday, who is an artist who has been\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://pitchfork.com/artists/debby-friday/\"\u003eprofiled on Pitchfork\u003c/a\u003e. She has a very cool blend of RnB and experimental electronic music that is both challenging and inviting. I’m really looking forward to catching her set.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIf you were a touring musician what would be on your rider?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI am into junk food whenever I am traveling, so probably some healthy snacks would be the wisest choice for me. But, to be honest, I’ll probably have a crunchwrap supreme on there as well.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e","publishedDate":"2024-03-11T04:00:00.000Z","isFeatured":false,"isHidden":false,"tag":null,"createdAt":"2024-03-07T22:49:01.327Z","updatedAt":"2024-03-19T17:53:56.946Z","publishedAt":"2024-03-11T20:03:35.263Z","locale":"en","Image":{"data":{"id":5278,"attributes":{"name":"SethHeadShot (1).JPG","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":3024,"height":3024,"formats":{"large":{"ext":".JPG","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/large_Seth_Head_Shot_1_e4078e5c91.JPG","hash":"large_Seth_Head_Shot_1_e4078e5c91","mime":"image/jpeg","name":"large_SethHeadShot (1).JPG","path":null,"size":124.47,"width":1000,"height":1000},"small":{"ext":".JPG","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/small_Seth_Head_Shot_1_e4078e5c91.JPG","hash":"small_Seth_Head_Shot_1_e4078e5c91","mime":"image/jpeg","name":"small_SethHeadShot (1).JPG","path":null,"size":41.44,"width":500,"height":500},"medium":{"ext":".JPG","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/medium_Seth_Head_Shot_1_e4078e5c91.JPG","hash":"medium_Seth_Head_Shot_1_e4078e5c91","mime":"image/jpeg","name":"medium_SethHeadShot (1).JPG","path":null,"size":77.77,"width":750,"height":750},"thumbnail":{"ext":".JPG","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/thumbnail_Seth_Head_Shot_1_e4078e5c91.JPG","hash":"thumbnail_Seth_