ditor at Glamour.de. In summer 2021, I became a full time editorial writer for Glamour and left Photoshop once and for all behind.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eNow I am the Senior Cultural Editor at Glamour Germany, still writing about basically everything apart from beauty and fashion content, i.e. tv shows, movies, stars, career, travel, dating and relationships, food and drink. I also focus on all things empowerment for Glamour Germany: What does the state of women look like? How can we reach equality? What are the biggest challenges for women everywhere in the world?\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow do you describe your job to friends and family?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eEasy! It’s the best job I could wish for. I get to watch tv shows and movies, interview actors and celebrities and, most importantly, I can write about things that may make the world a better place for generations to come. I am very happy that Glamour chose to make female empowerment their main focus –\u0026nbsp;this allows me to not be silent about inequalities and injustice, but rather speak out –\u0026nbsp;and imagine, all the world is listening.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThis year will be the first Glamour Women of the Year Awards on November 2 in Germany. What does something like this mean for the brand?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eIt’s long overdue to present women with an award like Glamour WOTY in Germany. We are happy 