development team and in charge of measuring performance and providing insights to improve the relationship between readers and the brand. In a nutshell,\u0026nbsp; I don’t write articles anymore but write lots of reports.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eINMA recently named you as one of the “\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.inma.org/Initiatives/30Under30/\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cu\u003e30 Under 30\u003c/u\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e” for the data category – what was your reaction to being nominated?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e“Wow!” It's something I couldn't have imagined when I first moved to London nearly five years ago. It's a sense of accomplishment.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhen did you realize you wanted to make the switch to analytics?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eIt happened naturally and I had an analyst title when I realised. When I joined the audience development team, I had no prior knowledge of data analytics. Fortunately, I met my mentor, Aru Fukuda, who taught me data analytics from scratch. I learned a lot from him and now the spreadsheet is my best friend.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat is your favorite part of your role?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eI enjoy writing reports; it feels similar to being an editor, except instead of people, I work with numbers. My role is to provide context to numbers and explain the trends we're observing. Visuals are also needed for structuring and enhancing understanding. It's like conducting an interview through data.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWho is someone that inspires you? Why?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eMy grandmother is a huge inspiration to me. She's in her 90s and still drives a car – she's a badass! No matter what obstacles come her way, she maintains grace, strength, and confidence.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhere do you see yourself in five years?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eThere is a career development idea called 'VSOP,' which stands for Variety in the 20s, Specialty in the 30s, Originality in the 40s, and Personality in the 50s. Now that I’m turning into the Speciality phase, I want to focus on developing my skills in content analytics.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhen you’re not working, how do you spend your free time?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eSauna and eating out. I usually kick off the weekend with a morning sauna session with friends. Then, explore new restaurants — my Google Maps is quite a mess with all the pins from these adventures.\u