ectives and points of views, and exchange ideas to create great content.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow do you describe your job to friends and family?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eAgainst all odds, my job isn’t glamorous! It really is about sorting out logistics, reading, editing, working on spreadsheets, memorising collections, identifying trends, and lots of window shopping (very bittersweet)! Oops, and I almost forgot… replying to many, many emails. Hey, this IS the real fashion deal!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThis month is Hispanic Heritage month. What does it mean to you?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eNow, more than ever, we have to embrace our culture, our roots, our talent, our people. Our history and traditions have served as inspiration to many artistic, cultural, and gastronomic movements, all of which have had a great impact on the world at large. If there is one thing that truly identifies us as Hispanics/Latin Americans, it is most definitely our organic ability to create (wherever we find ourselves in the world) a tight and supportive community: una familia.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat does a typical work day look like for you?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;\"\u003eEveryday is different! One day I could find myself writing a piece or editing our shopping pages, the next I could be assisting at a shoot or I’