ondé Nast. I knew how much I wanted the job so in my mind, I kept telling myself, “you’ve got the chance, now don’t let it go (Thanks to HR, Priscila, Jim and Aaron).” And here we are. Making the dream come true.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow do you describe your job to friends and family?\u003c/strong\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eThe coolest job EVER! Something I can say about what I do as a designer at Condé Nast is that I’m able to give life (visually) to the words of the editors. When people see it, it makes them want to read and keep the magazine. Or the editors see the magazine and it makes them feel good and proud. That’s what makes me happy.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThis month is Hispanic Heritage Month. What does it mean to you?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eIt means to be proud of what you are and where you come from. Never forget your roots. That’s the way I see life because culture is what forms you as a person and it reflects in every aspect of your life.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIf you could instantly learn a new talent, what would it be?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eSculpture, but I’m also aware that more than talent, it’s the practice and perseverance that makes you good at something.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat was your dream profession growing up?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eI dreamt about two professions! The first one is what I’m actually doing, being a designer at a fashion magazine and the second one was being a rockstar. I always loved to play the guitar in front of an audience, it gets me nervous but also when the first song starts, it feels like there’s nothing else happening in the world. Just me, the guitar, the band and the songs. That\u0026nbsp; feeling also happens when I’m designing. It’s just me, the idea and the laptop. Everything that happens around me is in silence and slow motion.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat is something you have always wanted to do but haven’t done yet?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eDesign clothes. When I was in high school I made two t-shirts from scratch and used to customize my jeans and jackets. At some point, I would like to wear only clothes that I have made!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat is your favorite visual campaign that has ever been done by a brand? Why?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eThe Calvin Klein campaign! In my opinion, no other brand went that far before but that’s the thing with campaigns and doing something visual. You have to innovate, be provocative, don’t be afraid, make it simple but make something that you will remember forever. You don’t need a big and expensive production, maybe just Calvin Jeans and boxers on a model and that’s it!\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat is your proudest professional accomplishment?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eWell, it comes this October. I designed my first print cover at Condé Nast for GQ Mexico with Gael Garcia on the cover. He is one of the actors that led the new mexican cinema in the 2000’s with Amores Perros or Y Tu Mamá También. But in a more “romantic” way, my proudest professional accomplishment would be to inspire others to get deeper than the obvious and use conceptualization, arts and crafts and more DIY. Whatever is in your mind,you can do it. That’s the way to be different from others.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat is the best piece of advice you have ever received?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eWhatever you want to do, be the best at it. Always be kind to people and show a big smile.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFinally, you are a tour guide for a day. Where would you take tourists who have never visited Mexico before?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eMaybe it’s because I have lived near it all my life but Coyoacán for me is the perfect spot for everything and anyone at any age. I go every weekend to buy records with my supplier, buy handicrafts, drink some coffee and just sit there enjoying the day. Coyoacán has everything – museums, parks, cathedral, vintage stores, handicrafts, food for every mood and a lot of coffee shops. For me Coyoacán defines perfectly what Mexico is, a lot of color, kind people, very good food and a sense of calm.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","publishedDate":"2023-10-02T11:00:00.000Z","isFeatured":false,"isHidden":false,"tag":null,"createdAt":"2023-10-09T02:15:29.804Z","updatedAt":"2023-10-09T02:15:33.413Z","publishedAt":"2023-10-02T12:58:32.584Z","locale":"en","Image":{"data":{"id":4144,"attributes":{"name":"Screenshot 2023-10-02 at 13.33.34.png","alternativeText":null,"caption":null,"width":986,"height":1092,"formats":{"large":{"ext":".png","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/large_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d.png","hash":"large_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d","mime":"image/png","name":"large_Screenshot 2023-10-02 at 13.33.34.png","path":null,"size":1866.49,"width":903,"height":1000},"small":{"ext":".png","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/small_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d.png","hash":"small_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d","mime":"image/png","name":"small_Screenshot 2023-10-02 at 13.33.34.png","path":null,"size":500.47,"width":451,"height":500},"medium":{"ext":".png","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/medium_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d.png","hash":"medium_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d","mime":"image/png","name":"medium_Screenshot 2023-10-02 at 13.33.34.png","path":null,"size":1096.27,"width":677,"height":750},"thumbnail":{"ext":".png","url":"https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/thumbnail_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d.png","hash":"thumbnail_Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d","mime":"image/png","name":"thumbnail_Screenshot 2023-10-02 at 13.33.34.png","path":null,"size":52.01,"width":141,"height":156}},"hash":"Screenshot_2023_10_02_at_13_33_34_718b9c593d","ext":".png","mime":"image/png","size":566.42,"u