alk about all the good stuff, like what bits of the events I think will really appeal to people, new goals we’ve set and the things that challenge me. I love a good challenge! Each event is a very different beast and we try to shake up the content each year, so there are always new and unexpected things happening with the planning and communication. It's these unknowns that make it both challenging and enjoyable, so there’s plenty to talk about!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGQ Taiwan recently celebrated its second edition of ‘Style Fest.’ How was the event and what were your favorite takeaways?\u0026nbsp;\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eThis year's GQ Style Fest went from a one-day affair last year to a full two days this year, which presented some pretty big challenges that I’m happy to say we overcame! One thing we focused on this year was really fleshing out our target audience profiles. We have managed to attract a core audience of young people who are passionate about style culture, and who have a genuine interest in the brands we invited to participate. One of the most intriguing takeaways was that, while this year’s attendees were generally younger than the people who came last year, they also had more purchasing power.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThis year’s event saw double the sponsorship and triple ticket sales in comparison to its inaugural year. What does this mean for future Style Fest’s?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eYes, we saw a big jump in consumer revenue! Last year was about making a splash in the market, and this year we were able to gather even more accurate data about our target audience. This bodes well for the future, especially as the participating brands were happy with their sales. It seems that GQ Style Fest has hit a sweet spot for both consumers and brands.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAre there any other upcoming events and projects from GQ Taiwan that are in progress? Can you tell us a little bit about them?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eWith GQ Style Fest done and dusted, we have moved our preparations to GQ Urban Camping Festival and MOTY up a gear. One of the highlights of this year’s camping event, which we hold every autumn, is how it will showcase a mix of Taiwanese, Japanese, Korean, and Western influences. MOTY will also feature celebrities from overseas this year, which is equally exciting!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYou have worked on previous projects such as GQ Taiwan’s Suit Walk. What is your favorite part of putting an event together? What is the most difficult part?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eI really enjoy how GQ Taiwan's events cover a wide range of interesting themes, from style and suits, to outdoor living and parties. So every time we plan different projects, there’s ample room for letting our imaginations fly and coming up with new ideas. I love working with new brands and partners, and value the teamwork that events rely on to be successful. As the project manager, although there are lots of details that need my attention, it’s even more important to make sure everyone is communicating and pulling in the same direction. When that synergy happens, with colleagues and external partners alike, it’s a wonderful thing, and the key to holding a fantastic event!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOutside of work, what has been your most favorite event to attend? Why?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eIt’s not an event per se, but outside of work I've been studying animal communication with a view to perhaps one day, in the distant future, become an animal communicator. I adopted a dog a few years ago and became curious about the animal world and how different it is. I’ve been able to help people understand their pets better. Again, it’s all about communication, and bridging the gaps, which is something I clearly enjoy!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIs there an event you have always wanted to go to but never had the chance to?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003eI've always wanted to go to the Summer Sonic Festival in Japan. It has a different vibe to the many other music festivals in Taiwan. Summer Sonic leans more towards Western artists and an urban music festival style. The lineup always has loads of big international names that create a buzz and I’d love to experience the excitement and atmosphere that it creates. Maybe next year!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat can we hope to see from 